//	******************** DETECTORS OPTIONS ********************

//  Extra time added to detectors' time window and accounting for trigger
// jitter (In ns. Default is 0. In case of triggers superposition worse
// contributor takes precedence
//  Trigger resolutions are declared to be = 1ns (preliminarily, for the main,
// physics, ones, as of 2008/12, cf. "$COMPASS_FILES/maps/2008.xml/DAQ.xml"). 
// Therefore, in principle, no need for extra time, so more so as time gates for
// scifis have been wide opened. But we want to rescue those events
// corresponding to the 2nd time peak, where the timing of the trigger is 
// defined by an accidental coincidence (possibly due to bad debunching), cf.
// "http:://wwwcompass.cern.ch/compass/weekly/2008/plot_080829/talks_080829.pdf"
// There is also the case of the BT, which seems to be misaligned by -4ns. In
// these 2 cases, what we would need is an extension of the time gate in only
// one direction, that toward the past, but this is not available yet...
//			DT0	DT1	DT2	CT1	CT2	VI	VO	BT	aBT
Trigger ExtraTimeWidth  5	5	5	5	5	0	0	5	0

FI01X1__ HitTime [0-1] -5.00 5.00  	// SciFI: Time Cut (in ns)
FI01Y1__ HitTime [0-1] -5.00 5.00
FI05X1__ HitTime [0-1] -8.00 8.00
FI05Y1__ HitTime [0-1] -8.00 8.00
FI08X1__ HitTime [0-1] -8.00 8.00
